abstract: Rescue workers halted their efforts this afternoon to search the waters of the Mississippi River for dozens of people still missing after strong currents blocked their work.
snippet: Rescue workers halted their efforts this afternoon to search the waters of the Mississippi River for dozens of people still missing after strong currents blocked their work.
lead_paragraph: Rescue workers halted their efforts this afternoon to search the waters of the Mississippi River in Minneapolis for dozens of people still missing in the wreckage of a collapsed highway bridge after strong currents blocked their work.

abstract: An Interstate highway bridge in downtown Minneapolis loaded with rush-hour traffic dropped more than 60 feet into the Mississippi River, sending at least 50 vehicles and passengers into the water.
snippet: An Interstate highway bridge in downtown Minneapolis loaded with rush-hour traffic dropped more than 60 feet into the Mississippi River, sending at least 50 vehicles and passengers into the water.
lead_paragraph: An Interstate highway bridge in downtown Minneapolis loaded with rush-hour traffic dropped more than 60 feet into the Mississippi River last night, sending at least 50 vehicles and passengers into the water.

abstract: Only six months after winning their seats, new members find is Congress even more unpopular than President Bush.
snippet: Only six months after winning their seats, new members find is Congress even more unpopular than President Bush.
lead_paragraph: Think about it this way: You want a job really, really badly, more than you ever wanted anything. You devote months to pursuing the position, working around the clock, enduring the worst kind of scrutiny and criticism and spending tens of millions of dollars that were excruciatingly hard to come by.

abstract: Three moderate Democratic freshmen are complicating efforts by President Bush and Senate leaders to pass a proposed immigration measure this week.
snippet: Three moderate Democratic freshmen are complicating efforts by President Bush and Senate leaders to pass a proposed immigration measure this week.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, June 27 — In narrowly winning her seat last year, Senator Claire McCaskill of Missouri ran hard against what she saw as a flawed approach in Congress to dealing with illegal immigration. Ms. McCaskill, a Democratic newcomer, says she is not about to change her view now.
headline_main: New Senators Resist Overhaul of Immigration
headline_print_headline: New Senators Resist Overhaul Of Immigration

abstract: Climate change is not a hoax. The hoax is that we are really doing something about it.
snippet: Climate change is not a hoax. The hoax is that we are really doing something about it.
lead_paragraph: When you watch a baby being born, after a difficult pregnancy, it is so painful and bloody for the mother it is always hard to tell the truth and say, “Gosh, that baby is really ugly.” But that’s how I feel about the energy legislation passed (and not passed) by the Senate last week.

abstract: WASHINGTON — President George W. Bush had barely left the Capitol after immigration talks there Tuesday when Senator Harry Reid of Nevada, the majority leader, walked onto the Senate floor to call for a moment of silence. It was time, Reid said, to pay tribute to American soldiers in Iraq as their death toll reached 3,500.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President George W. Bush had barely left the Capitol after immigration talks there Tuesday when Senator Harry Reid of Nevada, the majority leader, walked onto the Senate floor to call for a moment of silence. It was time, Reid said, to pay tribute to American soldiers in Iraq as their death toll reached 3,500.
headline_main: Democrats vow to revive debate over Iraq war
headline_print_headline: Democrats vow to revive debate over Iraq war

abstract: It has been nearly three weeks since Democrats have held a formal Iraq debate or voted on an Iraq proposal and in that time, Congressional approval ratings have fallen.
